    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast the peppers</strong></p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6.</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>Romano pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon).</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> pepper</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 minutes or until softened.</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
