      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the jumbo prawns</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> garlic</strong> and cook for 30 seconds or until fragrant.</p>\n<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>jumbo king prawns</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(Can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook for 1-2 minutes. </p>\n<p>Add the<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>.</p>\n<p>Cook for 2-3 minutes further or until the prawns are cooked through.</p>\n<p> </p>",
